The Innovation & Engineering Hub by Volkswagen Group Services, in Portugal, delivers groundbreaking solutions together with our stakeholders, by developing sustainable and market-oriented products as well as innovative services.

Volkswagen Group Service is positioned in the market with a broad range of automotive services and supports the core business of Volkswagen, other brands and organizations.

Side by side with MAN Truck & Bus, one of Europe's leading manufacturers of commercial vehicles, we are hiring a dedicated team in our Hub. 🚚

MAN Truck & Bus is focusing on four key areas


Alternative drive systems;
Digitalization;
Automated driving;
Road Security;


Thus transforming itself from a commercial vehicle manufacturer to a provider of intelligent and sustainable transport solutions.

About The Team

Our MDM team is revolutionizing the automotive landscape with a robust and scalable platform, ensuring the rapid deployment of new products and services to vehicles. We prioritize our customers' needs, delivering state-of-the-art solutions using agile practices. Our mission is to optimize end-to-end delivery, ensuring a continuous stream of value.

Your responsibilities:


Lead the development, testing, deployment, and maintenance of backend solutions and internal tools using modern cloud infrastructure in the automotive IoT context;
Drive the implementation and maintenance of functionality for our trucks using agile methodologies, significantly contributing to our technical roadmap;
Design and create products, prototypes, and MVPs for near-vehicle services;
Architect and manage cloud-native microservices using containers, serverless functions, RESTful APIs, and event streaming;
Take full ownership of the products you build, including validating compatibility with embedded systems using hardware test setups;
Provide expert advice to your team and other teams on backend and tool development in an automotive IoT environment, continuously improving service, tooling, and processes;
Proactively identify and solve problems, acting as the interface between electrical engineers, IT technology, and users;
Embrace a results-oriented approach with a commitment to learning new technologies and solving problems innovatively.


Your skills:


Bachelor's degree in related field or comparable job expertise
Extensive Experience: Over 3 years of backend development experience, demonstrating advanced knowledge and leadership in the field;
Java/Kotlin Expertise: Deep expertise in backend development using Java/Kotlin, with significant focus on RESTful APIs and event-driven architecture (e.g., Kafka, Kinesis, SQS, MQTT);
Framework Proficiency: Mastery of frameworks, particularly Spring Boot, with the ability to leverage its full capabilities;
Database Management: Advanced knowledge and experience with SQL and NoSQL database management systems, capable of designing and optimizing complex database solutions;
Cloud Services Mastery: Extensive experience with cloud services (preferably AWS), including cloud paradigms such as Infrastructure-as-Code, PaaS, alerting, and monitoring, with a proven ability to integrate and optimize these services;
CI/CD and Microservices: In-depth experience in designing, implementing, and managing CI/CD pipelines and microservice architectures;
Software Principles: Solid understanding and application of Clean Code and Clean Architecture principles, with a strong emphasis on quality, maintainability, and usability.


What can we offer?


Attractive remuneration
Flexible work hours and hybrid mode
Attractive workspace
Active Health Care
Employee Benefits


For more information on our data processing activities and your rights as a data subject, please consult our privacy policy.

Ref: Level A
